data.description: NEW FLOORING, SOLAR PANELS, and NO backyard neighboring homes (a peaceful experience)!  Come see it for yourself.  Interested? Read on...3 bedroom, 2 bath Pulte home is a single-story, open floor plan.  When you walk in, to your immediate left there is a flex room (office, sewing room, or playroom - you decide).  As you continue down the entryway, the view of the combined kitchen, dining, and living space (framed by crown molding) makes for an inviting entertainment area.  The addition of the wood-burning fireplace will offer a cozy space you, your friends and your family will enjoy.  The kitchen has an island and ample granite countertop space.  The home receives beautiful morning sunlight in the dining area and backside of the home.  Later-day sunlight lands on the guest bedroom side of the home.  The primary bedroom is peaceful, private, inviting, and filled with natural light from the windows that also offer a great view of the large trees in the field behind the home. The primary bedroom is spacious and has a long walk-in closet as well as a primary bathroom with a granite countertop, a separate shower, and a soaker tub to relax after a long day.  The front yard has a covered porch with a good view of the neighborhood and the backyard has a privacy fence, a covered patio, and a great view of good country, Texas living. The neighbors are great and the yards are well-kept. There is also a park and pool in the neighborhood as well as an elementary and middle school within walking distance for the older kids.  The house is extremely well-kept and gently used and is just a few minutes away from downtown Georgetown. Schedule your tour today!
